1 2. Upon receipt of a notice for an examination or notice of authorization to participate in
2 the voluntary disclosure program under section 47-30.2-55, a holder shall retain, until
3 the conclusion of the examination or any related appeal or litigation, or the conclusion
4 of authorized voluntary disclosure in each instance, all relevant records dating back
5 ten years from the commencement of the examination, plus the applicable dormancy
6 period under section 47-30.2-04, before the date of the administrator's delivery of a
7 notice of an examination to a holder under this chapter.
8 3. The holder may satisfy the requirement to retain records under this section through an
9 agent.
10 4. The records must contain:
11 a. The verifiable information required to be included in the report;
12 b. The date, place, and nature of the circumstances that gave rise to the property
