3 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 47-30.2-39 of the North Dakota Century Code is
4 amended and reenacted as follows:
5 47-30.2-39. (610) Periods of limitation and repose.
6 1. Expiration before, on, or after July 1, 2021, of a period of limitation on an owner's right
7 to receive or recover property, whether specified by contract, statute, or court order,
8 does not prevent the property from being presumed abandoned or affect the duty of a
9 holder under this chapter to file a report or pay or deliver property to the administrator.
10 2. The administrator may not commence an action or proceeding to enforce this chapter
11 with respect to the reporting, payment, or delivery of property more than seven years
12 after the holder filed a nonfraudulent report under section 47-30.2-21 with the
13 administrator. The parties may agree in a record to extend the limitation in this
14 subsection.
15 3. The administrator may not commence an action, proceeding, or examination with
16 respect to a duty of a holder under this chapter more than ten years after the duty
17 arose.
18 4. The periods of limitation established by this section are tolled by the earlier of the
19 administrator's delivery of a notice that a holder is subject to an examination or the
20 delivery of notice of authorization to voluntarily disclose property subject to this
21 chapter under section 47-30.2-55.
